article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 73, Cameron 42
article.story: SAN ANTONIO, Texas -- Demarco Stepter came off the bench to score 14 points and lead UTSA past Cameron 73-42 Tuesday night. Terry Fields and Omar Johnson added 11 points each for the Roadrunners (6-1). Johnson also had five assists, and Devin Gibson added seven points, nine rebounds and eight assists. Nathan Murray came off the bench to lead the Aggies with a game-high 18 points and six rebounds, shooting 6 of 8 from the field and sinking all six of his free-throw shots. Cameron committed 17 turnovers while forcing just eight. UTSA converted the miscues for 22 points, while Cameron scored seven points off turnovers. UTSA hasn't started a season at 6-1 since 1988. The Roadrunners outrebounded Cameron 37-27.
